            "title": "Pr\u00e1ticas pedag\u00f3gicas para mudan\u00e7as de concep\u00e7\u00f5es de defici\u00eancias e atitudes sociais em rela\u00e7\u00e3o \u00e0 inclus\u00e3o",
            "abstract": [
                "O livro Pr\u00e1ticas Pedag\u00f3gicas para mudan\u00e7as de concep\u00e7\u00f5es e defici\u00eancias e atitudes sociais em rela\u00e7\u00e3o \u00e0 inclus\u00e3o representa duas grandes contribui\u00e7\u00f5es para \u00e1rea da Educa\u00e7\u00e3o, em primeiro lugar a necess\u00e1ria compreens\u00e3o das quatro defici\u00eancias mais frequentes: defici\u00eancia auditiva, defici\u00eancia f\u00edsica, defici\u00eancia visual e defici\u00eancia intelectual. Em segundo lugar, a possibilidade de conhecermos e pensarmos pr\u00e1ticas pedag\u00f3gicas que podem com objetivos definidos a partir das sugest\u00f5es de um programa informativo, propiciar o desenvolvimento de mudan\u00e7as de concep\u00e7\u00f5es de defici\u00eancias e atitudes sociais em rela\u00e7\u00e3o \u00e0 inclus\u00e3o. Os principais resultados apresentados pelas autoras, Aline de Novaes Concei\u00e7\u00e3o e Maewa Martina Gomes da Silva e Souza, revelam que com a aplica\u00e7\u00e3o de um programa informativo relacionado com pr\u00e1ticas pedag\u00f3gicas inclusivas e com estrat\u00e9gias did\u00e1tico- metodol\u00f3gicas, \u00e9 poss\u00edvel constituir um ambiente escolar harmonioso e inclusivo",
                "The book Pedagogical Practices for Changing Conceptions and Disabilities and Social Attitudes towards Inclusion represents two major contributions to the field of Education, firstly the necessary understanding of the four most common disabilities: hearing impairment, physical disability, visual impairment and intellectual disability. Secondly, the possibility of getting to know and thinking about pedagogical practices that can, with defined objectives based on the suggestions of an informative program, facilitate the development of changes in conceptions of disabilities and social attitudes towards inclusion. The main results presented by the authors, Aline de Novaes Concei\u00e7\u00e3o and Maewa Martina Gomes da Silva e Souza, reveal that with the application of an informative program related to inclusive pedagogical practices and didactic-methodological strategies, it is possible to constitute a harmonious and inclusive school environment"
            ],
